The [[SPIM Registration]] plugin has been updated. The major change is a modularization into a registration and fusion part which allows different methods in the future. The other changes comprise:

* Added channel specific advanced and interactive bead-segmentation
* Improved timelapse registration including  [[SPIM Bead Registration#How timelapse registration works | graphical feedback and interactive reference timepoint selection]]
* Improved multi-channel fusion, the registration of one channel can be applied to other channels
* By default, overriding of axial and lateral calibration is possible
* Various transformation models are supported now: Translation, Rigid, Affine  

